<span style="font-weight: 400;">Globally, over 2.5 billion people have experienced a worm infection. Worm infection is prevalent in tropical and subtropical regions, with America, China, and East Asia having the most occurrences of the infection.</span>

<b>Worms in the body can cause:</b>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Fatigue</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Loss of appetite</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Nausea</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Weight loss</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Bloating</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Abdominal pain</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Stomach troubles</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">In severe cases, the infected person may start to pass the worms with the stool.</span>

<b>Who is prone to worms?</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Children are very susceptible to worms. Also, people with poor sanitation have a higher risk of getting infected with worms. People with weak immune systems and those living with HIV may be at higher risk.</span>

<b>Preventive measures</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Although it seems impossible to eliminate all likely sources of worms, it's important to take necessary precautions to avoid their developments.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Sanitation is one very important preventive measure to take. For example, people should ensure to wash their hands before and after using the toilet. It's also important to wash the hands before cooking or touching any food.Â </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Most intestinal worms get inside the body from the food we eat. With this, itâ€™s important to follow a healthy food practice:</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Carefully wash all vegetables and fruits.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Always use clean water only.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">When travelling to a location with poor sanitation, avoid contact with unclean water.</span>

